TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=460
TASK_TITLE=Allow Deployment role to merge PRs when Boss approves
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W4
TASK_DESCRIPTION=The Deployment role (pane 1.2) currently has a safety rule that blocks PR merging — it can only create PRs. This is too restrictive. When the Boss (acting on user instruction) explicitly requests a merge, Deployment should be allowed to do it. The flow should be: User tells Boss to merge → Boss dispatches to Taskmaster → Taskmaster tells Deployment → Deployment merges. The safety guard should distinguish between: (1) autonomous merge (still blocked — Deployment should never merge on its own) and (2) user-approved merge via Boss directive (allowed). Check on-pre-tool-use.sh and the Deployment agent definition for where this restriction lives. Update the guard to allow merges when the dispatch chain includes Boss approval.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W4: Update Deployment merge rules — allow Boss-approved merges:done\n2:W4.1: Research — find merge-blocking rules in Deployment agent def and on-pre-tool-use.sh hook:done\n3:W4.2: Implement — update Deployment agent def template to allow user-approved merges, regenerate .md:done
